<%= javascript_include_tag 'jquery.cycle.lite.1.0.min' %>
<%= javascript_include_tag 'jquery.lightbox-0.5.min' %>
<%= stylesheet_link_tag 'jquery.lightbox-0.5' %>
<script type="text/javascript">
   $j(function(){  // $(document).ready shorthand
      $j('#testimonials').cycle({
          delay:  5000,
          speed:  1000,
          timeout: 10000
      });
      $j('#gallery a').lightBox();
   });
</script>

<div id="container">
<div class="how-to">  
  
    <div class="sub-title">How does it work?</div>
      <ul style="">
        <li>Tell us about your purchase</li>
        <li>Provide us with your financial numbers<br/>
        <span style="font-size:14px;font-style:italic;">No Account numbers of anything required.</span></li>
        <li>We evaluate your financial health <br/>
        <span style="font-size:14px;font-style:italic;">
          against <%= link_to "some well-established money management guidelines", "#{DOMAIN}how",:class => 'how-to-link' %> <br/> and provide you with a report.
          </span>
          <span id="gallery" style="font-size:14px;font-style:italic;">
            <a href="images/report-1.png" title="">Sample Report #1</a>  | 
            <a href="images/report-2.png" title="">Sample Report #2</a>
          </span>
        </li>
         <li>Get a Clear Picture of your finances</li>
          <li>Make an informed decision</li>
      </ul>
</div>

<div class="right-container">
  <div class="starter-form">
        <div class="sub-title">Ask Your Question </div>
        <% form_tag('/questions/new') do %>
          <%= label_tag 'I want to' %><br/>
          <%= text_field_tag 'want_to_buy', '' , :size => 20, :maxlength => 200 %><br/>

          <%= submit_tag 'Can I Afford it Now?', :class => 'ask-button button' %>

        <% end %>
  </div>
  <div class="testimonials-title">Verdict from our users</div>
  <div id="testimonials">

    <div id="testimonial_1">
      I thought I was doing pretty good until the Expert pointed out that my Savings were not enough to cover the Emergency Fund.
      Had never thought of that. Thanks!
      <div class="author">Mike L.</div>
    </div>
    <div id="testimonial_2">
      It never occurred to me that a couple of hundred dollars less into my 401(k) per month would result in my nest egg going lower
      by $300K when I retire. Made me think twice.
       <div class="author">Lisa B.</div>
    </div>
    <div id="testimonial_3">
      I like it when [report] tells me the future value of the money that I am going to spend now.
       <div class="author">Paul A.</div>
    </div>
    <div id="testimonial_4">
      It is useful when the report tells me when I can afford the item approximately when I am denied.
       <div class="author">Ariel S.</div>
    </div>
    <div id="testimonial_5">
       It's good to confirm that all my bases are covered before making my purchase. The report does a fine job of giving me a quick summary.
       <div class="author">Kathy D.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>  
</div>

